@node "download" "Downloading files from Aminet"
@{b}ANetGUI/II@{ub} can download files from Aminet by two programs:
· @{u}@{b}AmFTP@{ub} and @{b}downloadfiles.rexx@{ub}@{uu} - the rexx script was not written by me so I cannot guarantee that it will work and download files correctly. I also do not use AmFTP, because I don't like it. But since a working script was sent to me, I decided to include it.

· @{u}@{b}FTPMount@{ub} and @{b}copyfiles.rexx@{ub}@{uu} - it is a better way in my opinion. Simply set the Aminet AmigaDOS path to @{i}FTP:<aminet_site>/pub/aminet @{ui}or @{i}FTP:aminet @{ui}(if you set the aminet site correctly in @{i}FTPMountDir/Hosts @{ui}directory). If you set this, you will also be able to view the .readme files from Aminet.
@endnode

@node "legal" "Legal issues of ANetGUI/II"
It's freeware. You can distribute it freely as long as no files are modified.

However if you do like it, you could (and shy shouldn't? :-) contact the@{" author " link "author"}.
@endnode

@node "ARexx" "ARexx commands"
ARexx port of @{b}ANetGUI/II@{ub} is @{b}ANETGUI@{ub}.

Command:  @{b}Quit@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: quits ANetGUI/II

Command:  @{b}New@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: Delete every entry

Command:  @{b}Load@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: loads list

Command:  @{b}Save@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: saves list

Command:  @{b}SaveAs@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: saves list as

Command:  @{b}GetEntries@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: gets number of entries

Command:  @{b}GetPath@{ub}
Template: @{b}ENTRY/N/A@{ub}
Function: Returns path of an entry (like@{i} util/boot/AStart21.lha @{ui})

Command:  @{b}GetDit@{ub}
Template: @{b}ENTRY/N/A@{ub}
Function: Returns the dir of an entry (like@{i} util/boot @{ui})

Command:  @{b}GetFile@{ub}
Template: @{b}ENTRY/N/A@{ub}
Function: Returns the name of an entry (like@{i} AStart21.lha @{ui})

Command:  @{b}GetSize@{ub}
Template: @{b}ENTRY/N/A@{ub}
Function: Returns the size string of an entry (like@{i} 17K @{ui})

Command:  @{b}GetDesc@{ub}
Template: @{b}ENTRY/N/A@{ub}
Function: Returns description of an entry

Command:  @{b}ReqFile@{ub}
Template: @{b}OLDFILE,TITLE,DIR/S,SAVEMODE/S@{ub}
Function: Opens Asl file request, returns the name and in RC if the user has cancelled the requester

Command:  @{b}ReqChoice@{ub}
Template: @{b}TITLE/A,BODY/A,GADGETS/A@{ub}
Function: Requests choice (returns chosen gadget as RC - 1,2,3, ... ,0)

Command:  @{b}Rescan@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: Rescans the directories list

@{jcenter}@{b}««« COMMANDS ADDED IN ANETGUI 3.32 »»»@{ub}
@{jleft}
Command:  @{b}Entries@{ub}
Template: @{b}N/A@{ub}
Function: Returns the number of entries (in @{b}result@{ub}, not @{b}rc@{ub})

Command:  @{b}Message@{ub}
Template: @{b}BODY/A@{ub}
Function: Shorter version of @{i}ReqChoice@{ui}, it doesn't need to enter @{b}TITLE@{ub} and @{b}GADGETS@{ub}

Command:  @{b}ReqString@{ub}
Template: @{b}CONTENTS,TITLE@{ub}
Function: String requester, returns the text in @{b}result@{ub} and if the user has cancelled in @{b}rc@{ub}

Command:  @{b}ReqNumber@{ub}
Template: @{b}CONTENTS/N,TITLE@{ub}
Function: Number requester, returns the number in @{b}result@{ub} and if the user has cancelled in @{b}rc@{ub}

Command:  @{b}LoadList@{ub}
Template: @{b}FILENAME/A@{ub}
Function: Loads the ANetGUI/II selected files list (w/o requester)

Command:  @{b}AppendList@{ub}
Template: @{b}FILENAME/A@{ub}
Function: Append the ANetGUI/II selected files list (w/o requester)

Command:  @{b}SaveList@{ub}
Template: @{b}FILENAME/A@{ub}
Function: Saves the ANetGUI/II selected files list (w/o requester)

Command:  @{b}AddEntry@{ub}
Template: @{b}FILENAME/A,DIRECTORY/A,SIZE/A,DESCRIPTION/A,POSITION/N@{ub}
Function: Adds an entry into selected list manually

Command:  @{b}RemEntry@{ub}
Template: @{b}POSITION/N/A@{ub}
Function: Removes an entry from the selected list

@{jcenter}@{b}««« COMMANDS ADDED IN ANETGUI 3.60 »»»@{ub}
@{jleft}
Command:  @{b}GaugeOpen@{ub}
Template: @{b}TITLE/A,MAX/N/A,CURRENT/N,INFOTEXT@{ub}
Function: Opens a gauge

Command:  @{b}Gauge@{ub}
Template: @{b}CURRENT/N/A@{ub}
Function: Changes the gauge's value

Command:  @{b}GaugeClose@{ub}
Template: N/A
Function: Closes the gauge

Command:  @{b}ExpandName@{ub}
Template: @{b}FILENAME/A@{ub}
Function: Expands the name of a file (for ANetGUI, useful with @{i}PROGDIR:@{ui})

Command:  @{b}FindFile@{ub}
Template: @{b}DIR/A,FILE/A@{ub}
Function: Checks if a file in a directory exists

Command:  @{b}DoFmt@{ub}
Template: @{b}FORMAT/A,ARGS/M@{ub}
Function: Uses {i}RawDoFmt()@{ui} to create an appropriate text format (always use %s, not %ld)

@{jcenter}@{b}««« COMMANDS ADDED IN ANETGUI 3.83 »»»@{ub}
@{jleft}
Command:  @{b}GetANetFTP@{ub}
Template: N/A
Function: Gets a globally set Aminet server

Command:  @{b}GetANetDir@{ub}
Template: N/A
Function: Gets a globally set Aminet server directory

Command:  @{b}GetANetPath@{ub}
Template: N/A
Function: Gets a globally set Aminet path (ie. for CDs)

Command:  @{b}GetANetDload@{ub}
Template: N/A
Function: Gets a globally set download directory

For example usage of these commands, see ARexx scripts in @{i}rexx @{ui}directory.

To configure the buttons left out (in the bottom right hand corner of main window), edit the file @{b}.buttons@{ub} in the ANetGUI directory. Its' first line is the number of columns in one line, then every pair of lines describes one button. The first line of a pair is the name of the button (can be underscored), the second one is the ARexx script.
@endnode

@node "history" "Historia ANetGUI/II"
History of @{b}ANetGUI/II@{ub}:

@{b}4.25@{ub} - added @{i}.readme @{ui}files viewing option on double-clicking

@{b}3.83@{ub} - added globally set Aminet addresses and paths.

@{b}3.73@{ub} - added and/or search method

@{b}3.69@{ub} - Added@{" ARexx " link "ARexx"}commands @{i}DoFmt@{ui}, @{i}FindFile@{ui} and @{i}ExpandName@{ui}.

@{b}3.60@{ub} - added gauge control in@{" ARexx " link "ARexx"}.

@{b}3.53@{ub} - increased the possibility up to 22 lists

@{b}3.51@{ub} - added possibility to make up to eight lists of files

@{b}3.32@{ub} - added some new@{" ARexx " link "ARexx"}commands

@{b}3.12@{ub} - optimised list cleaning up (works 2 times faster now)

@{b}2.204@{ub} - corrected second version. never published.

@{b}2.172@{ub} - first public release on Aminet

@{b}2.143@{ub} - added ARexx support

@{b}2.85@{ub} - added multiselect

@{b}2.51@{ub} - first fully working version

@{b}2.38@{ub} - added Drag-N-Drop

@{b}ANetGUI 1.121@{ub} - my own program to do just that, but dropped the project.
@endnode

@node "SetupANetGUI" "Program SetupANetGUI"
SetupANetGUI is used to operate on lists of files.

Skîada sië z dwóch kartek:
· @{b}Lists of files@{ub} - used to configure lists of files. Changes will be made after clicking on @{b}Apply Changes@{ub}.
· @{b}ARexx buttons@{ub} - used to configure ARexx buttons on the bottom of the ANetGUI window. Changes will be after clicking on @{b}Save buttons@{ub} button.
@endnode

